### Describe your change:
This PR adds the **Z-Algorithm**, an efficient string-matching algorithm that runs in $O(n + m)$ time. 

**Overview:**
The Z-algorithm finds all occurrences of a pattern $P$ in a text $T$ by constructing the Z-array, where each element $Z[i]$ represents the longest common prefix between the string and the suffix starting at index $i$.

**Why this is a good addition:**
- **Performance:** It is fundamentally more efficient than naive matching and often easier to implement/understand than KMP (Knuth-Morris-Pratt).
- **Quality:** This implementation uses strict type hints, follows PEP 8, and includes comprehensive doctests.
- **Pure Python:** No external dependencies.

